transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra at Score Blue.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Yes, my name is Jameson.

Speaker 2: I ordered some Viagra last month,

Speaker 1: which was just a one-time deal.

Speaker 2: Then I noticed that they sent me another batch yesterday.

Speaker 1: So it was only going to be for one time.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Would you please not send me any more?

Speaker 2: Of course, yeah. These are adjustable prescriptions.

Speaker 1: Let's just see what happened with yours

Speaker 2: and why you got yours monthly, okay?

Speaker 1: So can I get your full name, Mr. Jameson,

Speaker 2: and your date of birth?

Speaker 1: My first name is Louis, L-O-U-I-S.

Speaker 2: Last name Jameson, J-A-M-I-S-O-N.

Speaker 1: Date of birth is July 7, 1952.

Speaker 2: I appreciate that. Thank you.

Speaker 1: All right, so I'm looking at the prescription here.

Speaker 2: We usually order January 7 for the Viagra,

Speaker 1: 50 milligrams, quantity of 10.

Speaker 2: Ah, okay. All right, so I see what happened here.

Speaker 1: It looks like the doctor, Dr. Thomas Petone,

Speaker 2: wrote your prescription with refills

Speaker 1: due to the low milligram dosage.

Speaker 2: That's why you saw it go through the following month.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so, Mr. Jameson, you're not required

Speaker 2: or obligated to get these every month.

Speaker 1: This is a prescription, not a subscription.

Speaker 2: So if you wanted, you could retain access

Speaker 1: to the remaining refills under the prescription,

Speaker 2: which I see here are 10 refills.

Speaker 1: If you wanted, you could just pause it,

Speaker 2: and then that would allow you to call in

Speaker 1: and place orders as needed,

Speaker 2: should you want the prescription in the future.

Speaker 1: No, I don't want it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, on cancellation, yeah,

Speaker 2: so that's why I just wanted to make sure,

Speaker 1: just because you can either cancel it or pause it.

Speaker 2: Canceling it closes out the prescription altogether,

Speaker 1: so you would lose access to the remaining refills

Speaker 2: under the prescription.

Speaker 1: Any future orders would require a new health consultation survey

Speaker 2: and separate approval by doctor, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, I'll take care of that for you now.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Bye-bye.
